text: Located in the vibrant Downtown Boston Theatre District Area, this apartment offers a convenient urban living experience. Just a few steps away from the Orange Line Downtown Crossing, and a short walk to the Green Line Train Boylston Station and Red Line Train, you'll feel at home in this bustling neighborhood. The Commons Park is also just a few steps away, providing a perfect escape into nature. This apartment features two queen-size beds and a full-size sofa bed, accommodating up to five guests. The living room is cleverly converted to serve as both a bedroom and living room, offering flexibility and comfort. With a fully equipped kitchen and a full bathroom, you'll have everything you need for a comfortable stay. Laundry facilities are available in the building for a separate fee, and self flexible check-in adds to the convenience. While there is no parking on the premises, guests are responsible for finding parking in the area. Early check-in and late check-out are available for a small fee and can be requested through our portal, subject to availability. Laundry facilities in the building are available for a separate fee. Situated in the heart of Downtown Boston, this apartment is surrounded by excellent public transportation options, making it easy to explore the city. The Orange Line Downtown Crossing is just steps away, while the Green Line Train Boylston Station is a mere 2-minute walk. The Red Line Train is only 5 minutes away, ensuring you can reach any part of the city with ease. The nearby Commons Park offers a beautiful green space for relaxation. This apartment is subject to street noise due to its central location in downtown Boston, which can be lively at all hours. Smoking is not allowed inside the apartment or the building, and any attempt to throw a party will result in immediate termination. Pets are not allowed. The apartment is equipped with a doorbell camera for security purposes. Air conditioning is unavailable between October 15th and May 5th.
